{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"4a39c97d-1d70-4f16-a0d2-ff3b41f4378c","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest compatibility layer by default.**\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 4.0, projects are **Microsoft.Testing.Platform-native only**. The VSTest bridge adapter (`Microsoft.Testing.Platform.MSBuild`) that allowed `vstest.console` to discover and run tests is no longer included automatically.\n\n### Your options:\n\n1. **Re-enable the VSTest bridge** — add this to your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>true</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n   ```\n   Or more directly, add the `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.VSTestBridge` package.\n\n2. **Switch your CI to use `dotnet test`** (recommended) — the modern `dotnet test` command works natively with Microsoft.Testing.Platform. Replace `vstest.console` invocations with:\n   ```\n   dotnet test TestProject.csproj\n   ```\n\n3. **Pin to MSTest.Sdk/3.x** if you need more time to migrate.\n\nOption 2 is the recommended path forward — `vstest.console` is being phased out in favor of the new testing platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"ad7ba862-f201-4767-88f2-3e5470bcd20a","outputTokens":294,"requestId":"042B:29B12:2551E12:2A19FF7:69E8375B"},"id":"1d08315a-e729-425a-86ac-64516598e8f8","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:50:10.873Z","parentId":"68997600-14a7-45ef-a610-79f903609e3b"}
